<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 6:32PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Muscogee and
central Harris Counties through 700 PM EDT...
At 631 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Hamilton, moving
southwest at 20 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Pine Mountain, Ellerslie, Flat Rock, F.d. Roosevelt State
Park, Midland, Cataula, Fortson and Mulberry Grove.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
